SIMPLE: remorseful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remorseful
<hw>Re*morse"ful</hw> <pr>(-m?rs"f?l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of remorse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The full tide of <qex>remorseful</qex> passion had abated.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Compassionate; feeling tenderly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exciting pity; pitiable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*morse"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*morse"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remorseless</ent>⟦br⟧
